
00:00:01,635 --> 00:00:02,970
Narrator:
WELCOME TO THE SHARK TANK,

00:00:02,970 --> 00:00:05,539
WHERE ENTREPRENEURS
SEEK AN INVESTMENT

00:00:05,539 --> 00:00:07,975
TO START, GROW, OR SAVE
THEIR BUSINESS.

00:00:07,975 --> 00:00:09,142
HI, AGAIN, SHARKS.

00:00:09,142 --> 00:00:10,477
[ Singsong voice ]
HE'S BA-ACK.

00:00:10,477 --> 00:00:12,379
YOU'RE AMAZING.
I'M VERY IMPRESSED.

00:00:12,379 --> 00:00:13,814
THE POWER OF "SHARK TANK."

00:00:13,814 --> 00:00:15,549
I THINK
IT'S THE POWER OF YOU.

00:00:15,549 --> 00:00:18,652
Narrator: IF THE SHARKS HEAR
A GREAT IDEA...

00:00:18,652 --> 00:00:20,287
...THEY'LL INVEST
THEIR OWN MONEY...

00:00:20,287 --> 00:00:21,989
Herjavec:
YOU'RE THE REAL DEAL.

00:00:21,989 --> 00:00:23,490
YOU ARE PROBABLY
THE BEST ENTREPRENEUR
WE'VE EVER HAD HERE.

00:00:23,490 --> 00:00:26,126
YOU UNDERSTAND THE OFFERS?
$20 MILLION VALUATION.

00:00:26,126 --> 00:00:27,160
$13 MILLION.

00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:29,496
Narrator: ...AND FIGHT EACH
OTHER FOR A DEAL.

00:00:29,496 --> 00:00:31,398
YOU SAID IT WASN'T
ABOUT THE MONEY.

00:00:31,398 --> 00:00:33,000
THEY KEEP ON RESPONDING
BASED OFF THE MONEY.

00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,701
OH, THAT'S CRAP.
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

00:00:34,701 --> 00:00:37,304
THAT'S NOT TRUE.
Narrator: BUT THE ENTREPRENEURS
MUST GET THE FULL AMOUNT

00:00:37,304 --> 00:00:40,541
THEY'RE ASKING FOR, OR THEY'LL
WALK AWAY WITH NOTHING.

00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:43,944
ONE MOMENT IT WAS THERE,
AND THEN POOF, YOU LOSE A DEAL.

00:00:43,944 --> 00:00:44,978
NO, I'M SERIOUS.

00:00:44,978 --> 00:00:46,713
I'M SERIOUS, TOO.
NO. NOT HAPPENING.

00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:48,615
OH, MY GOD.

00:00:48,615 --> 00:00:50,918
Narrator:
WHO ARE THE SHARKS?

00:00:52,619 --> 00:00:57,524
THEY'RE SELF-MADE
BUSINESS EXPERTS WORTH BILLIONS.

00:00:57,524 --> 00:01:00,394
KEVIN O'LEARY IS
A SHREWD VENTURE CAPITALIST

00:01:00,394 --> 00:01:02,029
WHO MADE HIS FORTUNE

00:01:02,029 --> 00:01:04,097
SELLING A CHILDREN'S
EDUCATIONAL COMPANY

00:01:04,097 --> 00:01:06,533
FOR OVER $4 BILLION.

00:01:06,533 --> 00:01:10,370
DAYMOND JOHN DOMINATED
THE FASHION WORLD WITH FUBU.

00:01:10,370 --> 00:01:13,473
NOW HE'S THE BRANDING EXPERT
BEHIND MULTIPLE GLOBAL BRANDS

00:01:13,473 --> 00:01:15,509
GENERATING BILLIONS IN SALES.

00:01:16,543 --> 00:01:19,313
ROBERT HERJAVEC, SON OF
AN IMMIGRANT FACTORY WORKER,

00:01:19,313 --> 00:01:20,581
FOUNDED ONE OF

00:01:20,581 --> 00:01:24,418
THE WORLD'S PREEMINENT
CYBER-SECURITY FIRMS.

00:01:24,418 --> 00:01:28,488
LORI GREINER, THE QUEEN OF QVC,
HOLDS OVER 100 PATENTS

00:01:28,488 --> 00:01:30,090
AND HAS LAUNCHED
OVER 400 PRODUCTS,

00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:33,260
GROSSING OVER A HALF A BILLION
DOLLARS IN SALES.

00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:37,764
AND MARK CUBAN,
RENOWNED BILLIONAIRE TECH MOGUL

00:01:37,764 --> 00:01:41,735
AND THE OUTSPOKEN OWNER
OF THE DALLAS MAVERICKS.

00:01:50,143 --> 00:01:52,946
MY NAME IS DAVE ALWAN,
AND I'M FROM PEORIA, ILLINOIS.

00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:54,615
MY COMPANY IS ECHO VALLEY MEATS,

00:01:54,615 --> 00:01:56,984
AND WE SPECIALIZE IN THE BEST
MEAT PRODUCTS IN THE WORLD.

00:01:56,984 --> 00:01:58,285
THANK YOU.
HAVE A GREAT DAY.

00:01:58,285 --> 00:02:00,687
I ACTUALLY PITCHED MY BUSINESS
ON "SHARK TANK"

00:02:00,687 --> 00:02:03,123
A YEAR AND A HALF AGO
AND WALKED AWAY WITHOUT A DEAL.

00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:06,293
I CAN'T CALL YOUR BUSINESS PLAN
BAD BECAUSE THERE ISN'T ONE.

00:02:06,293 --> 00:02:09,363
YOU MAKE A GREAT PRODUCT, BUT
YOU'RE COMING IN UNPREPARED.

00:02:09,363 --> 00:02:11,198
THAT DOESN'T CUT IT.
I'M OUT.

00:02:11,198 --> 00:02:14,034
Alwan: I KEPT MY CHIN HIGH, BUT
INSIDE, IT WAS GUT-WRENCHING.

00:02:14,034 --> 00:02:16,670
I TRULY DIDN'T HAVE
A GOOD ENOUGH BUSINESS PLAN.

00:02:16,670 --> 00:02:19,339
I KNEW I HAD TO GO BACK
AND DIG DEEP INTO MY COMPANY,

00:02:19,339 --> 00:02:22,209
FIGURE OUT ALL MY COSTS, AND
COME UP WITH A BUSINESS PLAN,

00:02:22,209 --> 00:02:23,610
AND THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT I DID.

00:02:23,610 --> 00:02:25,912
SO, WE FINALLY GOT THIS REPORT
BACK FROM THE UNIVERSITY,

00:02:25,912 --> 00:02:28,315
AND NOW WE KNOW WHAT IT ENTAILS
TO ACQUIRE A NEW CUSTOMER.

00:02:28,315 --> 00:02:30,183
NOW THAT I HAVE
THE MARKETING SIDE DOWN

00:02:30,183 --> 00:02:32,986
AND MY CUSTOMER-ACQUISITION
COSTS DOWN, I KNOW MY NUMBERS.

00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:34,154
I AM EXCITED.

00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:35,255
I'M COMING BACK IN THE TANK

00:02:35,255 --> 00:02:36,490
BECAUSE I WANT A DEAL.

00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:38,759
MORE IMPORTANTLY,
I WANT A SHARK AS A PARTNER.

00:02:38,759 --> 00:02:40,193
THE SHARKS MIGHT HAVE GOT
THE BEST OF ME

00:02:40,193 --> 00:02:42,429
THE FIRST TIME AROUND,
BUT I CAN ASSURE YOU, THIS TIME,

00:02:42,429 --> 00:02:43,830
I'M GONNA BLOW THEM
OUT OF THE WATER.

00:03:02,983 --> 00:03:04,484
HI, AGAIN, SHARKS.

00:03:04,484 --> 00:03:07,120
I'M DAVE ALWAN OF ECHO VALLEY
MEATS FROM PEORIA, ILLINOIS.

00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:09,489
YOU MIGHT REMEMBER ME
FROM SEASON 4

00:03:09,489 --> 00:03:11,358
AND MY DELICIOUS MEAT PRODUCTS.

00:03:11,358 --> 00:03:13,360
[ Singsong voice ]
HE'S BA-ACK.
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:15,996
I DIDN'T GET A DEAL,
AND I WAS DEVASTATED,

00:03:15,996 --> 00:03:18,999
BUT I WALKED OUT THOSE DOORS,
HELD MY HEAD HIGH.

00:03:18,999 --> 00:03:21,234
YOUR TOUGH QUESTIONS
MADE ME GO HOME

00:03:21,234 --> 00:03:24,404
AND SCRUTINIZE MY BUSINESS AND
BECOME A BETTER ENTREPRENEUR.

00:03:24,404 --> 00:03:26,406
LAST TIME I WAS HERE,

00:03:26,406 --> 00:03:30,077
I WAS ASKING FOR $300,000
FOR 20% EQUITY.

00:03:30,077 --> 00:03:31,945
NOW I AM CUTTING IT IN HALF --

00:03:31,945 --> 00:03:36,583
$150,000 FOR THE SAME 20% EQUITY
IN MY BUSINESS.

00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:38,618
I AM HERE TO MAKE A DEAL.

00:03:38,618 --> 00:03:40,854
MY COMPANY, ECHO VALLEY MEATS,
SPECIALIZES

00:03:40,854 --> 00:03:43,156
IN THAT OLD-FASHIONED
BUTCHER-SHOP QUALITY,

00:03:43,156 --> 00:03:45,492
AND WE DELIVER THE MOST
DELICIOUS MEATS AND TREATS

00:03:45,492 --> 00:03:47,494
THROUGH OUR WEBSITE
AND GIFT CATALOG,

00:03:47,494 --> 00:03:50,063
AND I KNOW THE MEAT
BUSINESS BETTER THAN ANYONE.

00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:52,499
I CAN'T COME EMPTY-HANDED.

00:03:52,499 --> 00:03:53,366
ALL RIGHT.

00:03:53,366 --> 00:03:54,401
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:03:54,401 --> 00:03:56,670
Alwan:
I BROUGHT MY SON, JORDAN.

00:03:56,670 --> 00:03:59,840
IF I REMEMBER CORRECTLY,
THIS FOOD WAS DELICIOUS.

00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,241
YEAH.
YEAH?

00:04:01,241 --> 00:04:02,542
IT WAS AMAZING.
I REMEMBER IT.

00:04:02,542 --> 00:04:04,111
Cuban:
WE ORDER IT THANKSGIVING.

00:04:04,111 --> 00:04:05,112
WE ORDER IT EVERY CHRISTMAS.

00:04:05,112 --> 00:04:07,047
I EAT THOSE CHEESE
GARLIC SPREAD THINGS

00:04:07,047 --> 00:04:07,948
AND GAIN ABOUT 15 POUNDS.

00:04:07,948 --> 00:04:09,883
I HATE THOSE. DON'T BRING
THEM ANYWHERE NEAR ME.

00:04:09,883 --> 00:04:11,952
Alwan: HAND THEM OUT.
Greiner: [ CHUCKLES ]

00:04:11,952 --> 00:04:13,186
OH, THIS LOOKS GOOD.

00:04:13,186 --> 00:04:15,155
LADIES FIRST, PLEASE.
OH, THANK YOU.

00:04:15,155 --> 00:04:16,823
HERE WE GO AGAIN.
Herjavec:
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

00:04:16,823 --> 00:04:18,191
TO DIE FOR.

00:04:18,191 --> 00:04:19,092
MR. O'LEARY.

00:04:19,092 --> 00:04:21,061
THANK YOU, JORDAN.
THAT'S GREAT.
FOR YOU.

00:04:21,061 --> 00:04:22,395
I'M JUST GONNA START EATING,
DAVE. I'M NOT EVEN WAITING

00:04:22,395 --> 00:04:23,430
TILL THEY GET THEIRS.
PLEASE EAT.

00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:25,031
EVERYTHING ON THERE
IS MY OWN RECIPE.

00:04:25,031 --> 00:04:27,334
THESE ARE SO GOOD.
John: FANTASTIC.

00:04:27,334 --> 00:04:29,002
SEE YOU, JORDAN.
LATER, JORDAN.

00:04:29,002 --> 00:04:30,470
BYE, JORDAN.
BYE, JORDAN.

00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:32,672
COME BACK WITH MORE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:04:32,672 --> 00:04:34,841
WHAT HAPPENED TO SALES
AFTER YOU WERE ON THE SHOW?

00:04:34,841 --> 00:04:36,777
SALES, AFTER THE SHOW,
EXPLODED.

00:04:36,777 --> 00:04:39,646
BUSINESS HAS NEVER BEEN BETTER,
BUT I TOOK YOUR ADVICE

00:04:39,646 --> 00:04:42,816
AND REALIZED THE ONE OPPORTUNITY
I HAVE TO SCALE

00:04:42,816 --> 00:04:44,151
IS THE MAIL-ORDER INDUSTRY.

00:04:44,151 --> 00:04:46,019
IT'S NOT MY RETAIL,
AND IT'S NOT MY CATERING.

00:04:46,019 --> 00:04:48,088
WE DECIDED TO SPLIT
THE MAIL-ORDER OFF

00:04:48,088 --> 00:04:49,623
INTO ITS OWN ENTITY NOW.

00:04:49,623 --> 00:04:53,160
PRE-"SHARK TANK," LAST YEAR,
WAS ROUGHLY $190,000.

00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:55,896
RIGHT NOW, WE'VE BROKE
$1.4 MILLION IN OUR MAIL ORDER.

00:04:55,896 --> 00:04:57,330
Greiner: REALLY? WOW.
OH!

00:04:57,330 --> 00:04:58,999
JUST THE MAIL-ORDER.
JUST THE MAIL-ORDER ALONE.

00:04:58,999 --> 00:05:00,734
ARE YOU SELLING US TODAY
JUST THE MAIL-ORDER?

00:05:00,734 --> 00:05:01,868
JUST THE MAIL-ORDER,

00:05:01,868 --> 00:05:03,737
WHICH I FEEL HAS
THE MOST POTENTIAL TO SCALE.

00:05:03,737 --> 00:05:05,172
AH. THAT'S WHY YOU'RE ASKING
FOR LESS MONEY.

00:05:05,172 --> 00:05:07,541
AS I RECALL, LAST TIME
YOU WERE HERE, DAVE,

00:05:07,541 --> 00:05:09,142
WHERE YOU RAN INTO PROBLEMS

00:05:09,142 --> 00:05:11,144
WASN'T NECESSARILY
JUST VALUATION.

00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:12,946
YOU DIDN'T KNOW
YOUR CUSTOMER ACQUISITION COSTS.

00:05:12,946 --> 00:05:14,781
KEVIN, THAT NUMBER IS $12,

00:05:14,781 --> 00:05:16,049
BUT MORE IMPORTANTLY,

00:05:16,049 --> 00:05:17,784
IT ONLY COSTS $1
TO RETAIN THAT CUSTOMER.

00:05:17,784 --> 00:05:19,152
WE'VE HAD GREAT RETENTION --

00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:22,255
BETWEEN 35% AND 40% HAVE CAME
BACK AND ORDERED MULTIPLE TIMES,

00:05:22,255 --> 00:05:23,323
JUST LIKE MR. CUBAN.

00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:24,858
Greiner: REALLY?
YES.

00:05:24,858 --> 00:05:28,195
SO IN THE $1.4 MILLION,
WHAT WAS YOUR PROFIT OF THAT?

00:05:28,195 --> 00:05:31,097
UH, APPROXIMATELY
$260,000. 18.3%.

00:05:31,097 --> 00:05:33,967
IN THIS CALENDAR YEAR,
HOW MUCH CASH

00:05:33,967 --> 00:05:35,302
WILL THE MAIL-ORDER DIVISION

00:05:35,302 --> 00:05:37,704
THAT YOU'RE SELLING
THIS EQUITY IN GENERATE?

00:05:37,704 --> 00:05:39,673
WE ARE PROJECTING
ABOUT $1.8 MILLION

00:05:39,673 --> 00:05:42,042
WITH A NET OF APPROXIMATELY
$400,000.

00:05:42,042 --> 00:05:43,610
$400,000.

00:05:43,610 --> 00:05:44,911
THIS IS A GREAT STORY.

00:05:44,911 --> 00:05:46,980
YEP. DAVE, HOW MUCH HAS
THE RETAIL BUSINESS,

00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:48,148
THE OTHER BUSINESS,
GROWN?

00:05:48,148 --> 00:05:50,483
12%, 15%.

00:05:50,483 --> 00:05:52,686
IT DOES NOT NET QUITE AS MUCH
AS THE MAIL-ORDER BUSINESS.

00:05:52,686 --> 00:05:56,289
RETAIL IS ABOUT 10% TO 12%.
MAIL-ORDER'S 18.3%.

00:05:56,289 --> 00:05:59,025
MAN, YOU HAVE YOUR NUMBERS DOWN
THIS TIME.

00:05:59,025 --> 00:06:02,162
SO, LAST TIME YOU WERE HERE, ONE
OF MY ISSUES WAS COMPETITION,

00:06:02,162 --> 00:06:03,864
FIGHTING THE BIG GUYS.

00:06:03,864 --> 00:06:05,832
THAT'S RIGHT.
O'Leary: LET'S TAKE OMAHA.

00:06:05,832 --> 00:06:07,968
THEY DISCOUNT AGGRESSIVELY
JUST BEFORE THANKSGIVING.

00:06:07,968 --> 00:06:10,070
THEY DO IT AGAIN
TOWARDS THE HOLIDAYS.

00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:12,806
I MEAN, THEY MAKE
REALLY BIG OFFERS.

00:06:12,806 --> 00:06:14,341
SURE.

00:06:14,341 --> 00:06:16,376
AND THEY'RE ACQUIRING
CUSTOMERS THAT WAY.
IT'S VERY COMPELLING.

00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:18,144
Alwan: AND THAT'S WHAT
I'M GONNA DO WITH THE MONEY.

00:06:18,144 --> 00:06:19,779
IT GIVES ME A LITTLE BIT BETTER
BUYING POWER.

00:06:19,779 --> 00:06:22,148
PRIME RIBS AND HAMS
DIP AFTER EASTER

00:06:22,148 --> 00:06:25,285
BECAUSE NOBODY'S GONNA BUY
THOSE AGAIN UNTIL CHRISTMAS,

00:06:25,285 --> 00:06:27,787
SO WHEN THE MARKET SOFTENS,
I CAN THEN TAKE THAT CASH

00:06:27,787 --> 00:06:29,489
AND GET ALL OF MY INVENTORY
BOUGHT IN

00:06:29,489 --> 00:06:30,790
AT A LOWER TIME OF THE YEAR

00:06:30,790 --> 00:06:32,659
BECAUSE I KNOW THE MARKET
SO WELL.

00:06:32,659 --> 00:06:35,095
I'M JUST CURIOUS. HOW LONG
CAN YOU BUY INVENTORY AHEAD?

00:06:35,095 --> 00:06:36,897
THE USDA SAYS
THEY DON'T REALLY LIKE ANYTHING

00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:38,098
LONGER THAN A YEAR.

00:06:38,098 --> 00:06:40,267
SIX TO EIGHT MONTHS IS
REALLY MY RULE OF THUMB.

00:06:40,267 --> 00:06:43,470
Herjavec: IF YOU BUY IT ON THE
10th MONTH VERSUS THE 6th MONTH,

00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:44,804
DOES THE QUALITY CHANGE?

00:06:44,804 --> 00:06:46,973
NO, BECAUSE IT'S VACUUM-PACKED
INTO OUR FREEZER.

00:06:46,973 --> 00:06:48,975
YOU'RE AMAZING.
I'M VERY IMPRESSED.

00:06:48,975 --> 00:06:51,044
YOU'RE COMING BACK IN HERE,
LEARNING FROM THINGS,

00:06:51,044 --> 00:06:55,548
BUILDING YOUR BUSINESS
THAT BIG IN JUST A YEAR.

00:06:55,548 --> 00:06:57,050
IT'S THE POWER
OF "SHARK TANK."

00:06:57,050 --> 00:06:58,618
I THINK IT'S THE POWER
OF YOU.

00:06:58,618 --> 00:07:01,521
I LOVE PEOPLE
THAT LEARN FROM THEIR MISTAKES,

00:07:01,521 --> 00:07:04,291
BUT THERE'S ONE
LITTLE PROBLEM I HAVE.

00:07:04,291 --> 00:07:06,559
BECAUSE I'M NOT
A BIG MEAT EATER,

00:07:06,559 --> 00:07:08,995
I DON'T THINK
I'M THE BEST PARTNER

00:07:08,995 --> 00:07:10,830
TO GO INTO BUSINESS WITH YOU.

00:07:10,830 --> 00:07:12,098
I'M OUT.

00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:13,199
OKAY.

00:07:13,199 --> 00:07:15,535
Cuban: DAVE,
I'M TRYING TO FIGURE OUT --

00:07:15,535 --> 00:07:18,171
DOES IT MAKE SENSE
TO SPLIT THE BUSINESS?

00:07:18,171 --> 00:07:20,307
I'M NOT SURE IT DOES.

00:07:22,742 --> 00:07:24,611
O'Leary: OKAY, I'M GONNA MAKE
YOU AN OFFER. HERE IT IS.

00:07:24,611 --> 00:07:27,414
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU
THE $150,000 FOR 20%.

00:07:27,414 --> 00:07:28,982
I HAVE ONE OTHER COVENANT.

00:07:28,982 --> 00:07:32,018
I WANT YOU TO SELL MY WICKED
GOOD CUPCAKES ON YOUR SITE.

00:07:32,018 --> 00:07:34,087
YOU'RE NOT GONNA DO IT
FOR FREE.

00:07:34,087 --> 00:07:36,289
I WANT AN ALLOCATION
OF THEIR PROFITS TO YOU, TOO,

00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:38,758
AND THAT HAS TO BE WORKED OUT
WITH THEM AS ENTREPRENEURS.
SURE.

00:07:38,758 --> 00:07:40,226
SO MY OFFER, IN SUMMARY,
IS THIS --

00:07:40,226 --> 00:07:42,696
I WILL GIVE YOU THE $150,000
FOR 20% OF THE WHOLE BUSINESS,

00:07:42,696 --> 00:07:44,431
AND I WANT MY WICKED CUPCAKES
ON YOUR SITE.

00:07:44,431 --> 00:07:45,865
Herjavec: WHOA.
WAIT A MINUTE.

00:07:45,865 --> 00:07:47,000
THE <i>WHOLE</i> BUSINESS.

00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,836
THE WHOLE BUSINESS?
YEP.

00:07:49,836 --> 00:07:51,071
OH.

00:07:51,071 --> 00:07:53,673
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO SPLIT
YOUR BUSINESS UP.

00:07:53,673 --> 00:07:54,808
THAT'S THE PROBLEM.

00:07:56,076 --> 00:08:01,648
DAVE, I'LL GIVE YOU $300,000
FOR 35%.

00:08:01,648 --> 00:08:04,150
FOR THE WHOLE COMPANY?
A PIECE OF EVERYTHING?

00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,952
THE WHOLE STRUCTURE.

00:08:07,187 --> 00:08:10,156
ROBERT,
$300,000 FOR 35%?

00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:14,160
KEVIN IS $150,000
FOR 20%.

00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,729
O'Leary:
I MAY MODIFY MY OFFER.

00:08:15,729 --> 00:08:18,365
I'LL PAY YOU $150,000
FOR 17.5%,

00:08:18,365 --> 00:08:20,500
WHICH I THINK MATCHES
ROBERT'S VALUATION.

00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:21,501
YEP.

00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:23,970
BUT I STILL WANT
MY CUPCAKES ON YOUR SITE.

00:08:23,970 --> 00:08:25,005
OF BOTH BUSINESS COMBINED?
YES, YES, YES.

00:08:25,005 --> 00:08:27,640
HE'S OFFERING THE SAME VALUE
I AM, JUST LESS CASH.

00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:30,577
BUT HE DOESN'T HAVE TO GIVE UP
AS MUCH OF HIS FAMILY BUSINESS.

00:08:30,577 --> 00:08:32,445
HOW DO YOU ALLOCATE
YOUR TIME

00:08:32,445 --> 00:08:34,280
BETWEEN THE TWO DIFFERENT
COMPANIES?

00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,049
YOU PRIORITIZE IT,
IS WHAT YOU HAVE TO DO.

00:08:36,049 --> 00:08:38,084
YOU SURROUND YOURSELF
WITH GREAT EMPLOYEES,

00:08:38,084 --> 00:08:40,987
WHICH IS WHAT I'VE DONE,
AND YOU START TO DELEGATE.

00:08:40,987 --> 00:08:43,490
MARK, ARE YOU INTERESTED
IN MAKING AN OFFER?

00:08:47,761 --> 00:08:53,433
SO, I'LL GIVE YOU $150,000 FOR
25% OF YOUR MAIL-ORDER BUSINESS,

00:08:53,433 --> 00:08:58,338
AND I WANT AN OPTION TO BUY
25% OF THE OTHER BUSINESS

00:08:58,338 --> 00:09:01,041
FOR THE SAME $150,000.

00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:03,877
IF EVERYTHING YOU SAY IS RIGHT

00:09:03,877 --> 00:09:07,414
AND THE RETAIL BUSINESS
NOT REALLY AN IMPACT, GREAT.

00:09:07,414 --> 00:09:09,049
IF IT TURNS OUT
YOU'RE SPLITTING YOUR TIME

00:09:09,049 --> 00:09:11,251
