OKAY.
YOU'RE DEAD TO ME.

00:39:18,022 --> 00:39:18,990
I'M OUT.

00:39:20,558 --> 00:39:23,228
IF I HAD TO TELL YOU SOMETHING
TO LEARN FROM THIS

00:39:23,228 --> 00:39:25,163
THAT I DO THINK
IS IMPORTANT,

00:39:25,163 --> 00:39:27,098
WE GET A LOT OF PEOPLE
IN HERE THAT SAY,

00:39:27,098 --> 00:39:28,933
"I'M FROM SILICON VALLEY,

00:39:28,933 --> 00:39:32,237
SO THEREFORE I'VE RAISED
MILLIONS OF DOLLARS."

00:39:32,237 --> 00:39:34,973
AND THEY'RE SO IN LOVE
WITH RAISING MONEY

00:39:34,973 --> 00:39:39,577
THAT THE BRASS TACKS OF ACTUALLY
SELLING SOMETHING GETS LOST.

00:39:39,577 --> 00:39:42,213
I'M OUT.

00:39:42,213 --> 00:39:45,550
DAYMOND IS
THE ONLY ONE LEFT.

00:39:45,550 --> 00:39:48,019
SO, HOW DO YOU THINK
YOUR NEGOTIATION STYLE

00:39:48,019 --> 00:39:49,153
HAS WORKED TODAY?

00:39:50,855 --> 00:39:52,223
UM...

00:39:52,223 --> 00:39:55,927
PROBABLY NOT THAT WELL.

00:39:55,927 --> 00:39:58,529
I HAVE NOTHING
AGAINST STRONG WOMEN.

00:39:58,529 --> 00:40:00,531
I DON'T CARE
IF YOU WERE A MALE UP HERE

00:40:00,531 --> 00:40:02,166
NEGOTIATING
THE SAME EXACT WAY.

00:40:02,166 --> 00:40:03,968
"OH, THAT'S NEVER
GONNA HAPPEN. OH."

00:40:03,968 --> 00:40:05,303
AND CORRECTING US
ALL THE TIME,

00:40:05,303 --> 00:40:07,071
'CAUSE WE JUST WANT TO GET
THE INFORMATION.

00:40:07,071 --> 00:40:09,274
I JUST DON'T THINK
IT WAS THE PROPER WAY.

00:40:09,274 --> 00:40:11,242
ON ONE SIDE, HONESTLY,

00:40:11,242 --> 00:40:15,146
I DON'T KNOW
IF I'VE SEEN BETTER DESIGNS.

00:40:15,146 --> 00:40:17,081
THANK YOU.
SO, UM...

00:40:17,081 --> 00:40:19,784
DAYMOND,
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

00:40:34,532 --> 00:40:36,067
Narrator:
FOUR SHARKS ARE OUT.

00:40:36,067 --> 00:40:38,903
DAYMOND IS CATALINA'S
LAST CHANCE

00:40:38,903 --> 00:40:42,607
TO MAKE A DEAL
FOR HER LINGERIE COMPANY NAJA.

00:40:42,607 --> 00:40:44,042
DAYMOND,
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

00:40:50,882 --> 00:40:56,287
YOUR VALUATION AT $10 MILLION --
I-I CAN'T COME CLOSE TO THAT.

00:40:56,287 --> 00:41:00,692
LOOK, WHEN YOU SAT DOWN
WITH THE V.C.s IN THE VALLEY,

00:41:00,692 --> 00:41:02,060
YOU HAD TO DO
SOME SORT OF PROJECTION.

00:41:02,060 --> 00:41:03,494
MM-HMM.
RIGHT?

00:41:03,494 --> 00:41:05,830
SO, ONE-YEAR, THREE-YEAR
PROJECTIONS IN SALES,

00:41:05,830 --> 00:41:06,998
WHAT DID YOU TELL THEM?

00:41:06,998 --> 00:41:08,433
WHAT ARE MY PROJECTIONS
FOR THIS COMPANY?

00:41:08,433 --> 00:41:09,500
OR DID THEY NOT CARE?

00:41:09,500 --> 00:41:11,002
AT THAT POINT,
THEY DIDN'T CARE.

00:41:11,002 --> 00:41:13,471
WOW.
THAT'S AMAZING.

00:41:13,471 --> 00:41:15,974
WHAT DO YOU PROJECT YOUR SALES
TO BE IN TWO YEARS?

00:41:15,974 --> 00:41:18,242
FOURT-- ABOUT $14 MILLION
IN REVENUE A YEAR.

00:41:19,911 --> 00:41:21,646
John: I'M JUST CURIOUS.
AND THEN THE YEAR AFTER?

00:41:21,646 --> 00:41:23,648
BUT WHERE DO YOU GET THAT
PROJECTION FROM? WAIT.

00:41:23,648 --> 00:41:25,750
I HAVE TO --
I HAVE TO SOBER THIS DOWN.
FROM THE AIR.

00:41:25,750 --> 00:41:29,420
I WONDER WHERE PEOPLE COME UP
WITH THESE REALLY HUGE,

00:41:29,420 --> 00:41:32,557
WHAT I CONSIDER
SOMEWHAT CRAZY PROJECTIONS.

00:41:32,557 --> 00:41:35,059
AND THIS HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH YOUR LINE.

00:41:35,059 --> 00:41:38,096
Herjavec: CATALINA,
DO YOU KNOW HOW HARD IT IS

00:41:38,096 --> 00:41:41,232
TO GO FROM $140,000
TO $14 MILLION?

00:41:41,232 --> 00:41:43,134
EVEN IN SILICON VALLEY,

00:41:43,134 --> 00:41:46,904
DO YOU KNOW HOW LONG IT TAKES
TO GET TO THAT LEVEL?

00:41:46,904 --> 00:41:48,873
ORACLE DIDN'T DO IT
IN THAT RATE.

00:41:48,873 --> 00:41:52,076
MICROSOFT DIDN'T DO IT
AT THAT RATE.

00:41:52,076 --> 00:41:54,946
THERE IS ALREADY MONEY IN THERE,
AND I THINK IT'S STUPID MONEY.

00:41:56,714 --> 00:41:58,950
AND I'M -- I'M MAD
THAT IT WAS VALUED AT THAT.

00:42:00,818 --> 00:42:03,988
BECAUSE I WOULD
HAVE BEEN ALL IN.

00:42:03,988 --> 00:42:06,958
SO, WITH THAT, I'M OUT.

00:42:09,894 --> 00:42:12,196
THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR YOUR TIME.

00:42:12,196 --> 00:42:13,431
GOOD LUCK.

00:42:18,002 --> 00:42:21,539
I JUST READ THIS NOTE
ON THE PANTIES, AND IT SAID,

00:42:21,539 --> 00:42:23,141
"I'M NOT WORTH
$10 MILLION."

